# Implementation Plan - Portal UI Hardening

## Goal

Restore the "Intelligence Registry" functionality by fixing the data mismatch between backend and frontend, and perform a full functional audit of the new sidebar-based UI.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py)

- Rename `/api/repair` to `/api/repair/thumbnails` to match frontend expectations.
- Ensure `/api/repair/library` handles both library sync and thumbnail healing as a comprehensive tool.
- Verify `/api/registry` correctly aggregates all sites from all regions.

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [regions.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/regions.js)

- Fix the logic in [renderSites()](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/regions.js#53-82) to use `this.sitesData` instead of the non-existent `this.regionsData`.
- Ensure category filtering correctly matches both `site.category` and `site.categories` array.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

- N/A (Manual/Browser verification preferred for UI features).

### Manual Verification

- **Registry View**: Open the Registry tab and verify the dense grid populates. Test search and filters.
- **Activity Monitor**: Start a download via Command Center and verify it appears in the Activity tab with progress.
- **Settings**: Change a setting (e.g., Log Level) and verify it persists on refresh. Trigger a Library Repair.
- **Video Deletion**: Delete a video from the player and verify it disappears from the Vault.
